Cross-Framework Design System built with Ionic + Stencil, designed for accessibility, theme flexibility, and reusable Web Components compatible with Angular, React, Vue, and Vanilla JavaScript.


# 🌐 Corporate Design System

A modern, reusable, and accessible **Design System** built with [StencilJS](https://stenciljs.com/) and [Ionic Framework](https://ionicframework.com/) to deliver **Web Components** ready for use across **Angular**, **React**, **Vue**, and **Vanilla JavaScript** applications.

---

## 📌 Project Goals

- ✅ Provide a consistent and scalable UI across corporate front-end apps
- ✅ Guarantee **accessibility** (WCAG 2.1 compliant wherever possible)
- ✅ Support **dark and light themes** using CSS custom properties
- ✅ Deliver reusable components via **Web Components**
- ✅ Make it framework-agnostic and easy to adopt

---

## 🧱 Technologies Used

| Layer        | Technology                  |
|--------------|-----------------------------|
| Components   | [Ionic](https://ionicframework.com/) + [Stencil](https://stenciljs.com/) |
| Styling      | [Sass (SCSS)](https://sass-lang.com/) with CSS variables |
| Documentation| [Storybook](https://storybook.js.org/) |
| Distribution | [NPM](https://www.npmjs.com/) |
| CI/CD        | GitHub Actions (optional)   |

---

## 🧩 Component Inventory (Initial Release)

The design system currently includes the following components:

- `ds-button`
- `ds-checkbox`
- `ds-input`
- `ds-card`
- `ds-radio`
- `ds-select`
- `ds-label`

Each component is customizable via props/attributes and follows accessibility best practices.

---

## 🎨 Theming

This design system supports **light** and **dark** themes using CSS variables. Consumers can switch modes by toggling a `data-theme` attribute on the root element:

```html
<body data-theme="light"> <!-- or "dark" -->
  <ds-button>Click me</ds-button>
</body>


